distinctive character because all are more or less globular and have digitiform, branching outgrowths. The new species may be part of the “mucronate-oxeote-styles bearing species” (i.e. 
<taxonomicName authority="Topsent, 1907" authorityName="Topsent" authorityYear="1907" box="[114,405,880,907]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="375" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="unicornis">
<emphasis box="[114,235,880,905]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="375">I. unicornis</emphasis>
Topsent, 1907
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest, 1996" authorityName="Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest" authorityYear="1996" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="375" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="timidum">
<emphasis box="[418,536,880,907]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="375">I. timidum</emphasis>
Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest, 1996
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest, 1996" authorityName="Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest" authorityYear="1996" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="6" pageNumber="375" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="tubiforme">
<emphasis box="[514,646,911,937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="375">I. tubiforme</emphasis>
Desqueyroux-Faundez &amp; Van Soest, 1996
</taxonomicName>
, as suggested by the latter authors in their 1996 paper).
</paragraph>
